### Test Authentication API

### 1. Register User
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "oldpassword123",
  "password_confirmation": "oldpassword123",
  "tc": true
}

### 2. Login User
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "oldpassword123"
}

### 3. Change Password (Replace YOUR_TOKEN with actual token from login)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/changepass
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "currentPassword": "oldpassword123",
  "newPassword": "newpassword456",
  "cfNewPassword": "newpassword456"
}

### 4. Test Login with Old Password (Should Fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "oldpassword123"
}

### 5. Test Login with New Password (Should Work)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "newpassword456"
}
